    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-08-30T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-08-30T07:00:00-05:00" n="1359"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1359">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">774.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/8–3054:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1359<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            type="from">Caffery</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-08-30T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 30, 1954—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>271. In light Egyptian rejection military assistance and limitations imposed by
                    Section 503 (b) (1) Mutual Security Act 1954,<note n="1" xml:id="d1359fn1">The
                        Mutual Security Act of 1954 was signed into law as Public Law 665 on Aug.
                        26, 1954. (68 Stat. 832)</note> I consider utmost importance US attitude re
                    economic assistance be framed produce maximum political impact here as well as
                    maintain and accelerate latent pro-West orientation present Egyptian
                    Government.</p>
                <p>Department doubtless appreciates that rejection military aid will inevitably be
                    interpreted in Egypt in manner unfavorable to US. Furthermore, continued US
                    efforts to encourage Iraqi participation area defense arrangements outside Arab
                    League framework will be interpreted as challenge to Egyptian leadership in
                        area.<note n="2" xml:id="d1359fn2">For documentation regarding U.S. efforts
                        to encourage Iraq’s participation in area defense arrangements, see <ref
                            target="#d1376">Documents 1376</ref> ff.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MGV1">Grant</persName> of substantial development
                    assistance would, however, appreciably mitigate these adverse reactions.</p>
                <p>Consequently, I request authority inform Egyptian Government in course
                    forthcoming economic negotiations US prepared provide up to 40 million dollars
                    during <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 55 provided adequately justified
                    projects submitted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
